descript.abstract: This polyline shapefile represents a 5 by 5 degree latitude/longitude grid covering the world with attributes that allow it to display grids at intervals of 5, 10, 15, 20, and 30 degrees. To display a grid with a 5-degree interval, simply display all of the lines. To display a coarser grid (e.g., a 15-degree interval), in the Layer Properties dialog box, set the DEGREE15 attribute value equal to Y.
descript.purpose: This layer is intended for researchers, students, and policy makers for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.

dataqual.logic: The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format using either tools in ArcGIS or ESRI SDC Data Development Kit Professional 2 (DDKP2). The SDC data set is then imported into a file geodatabase to verify and validate the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.

horizpa.horizpar: The geospatial part of this data set was mathematically generated using the ARC/INFO GRID? extension. In this manner, the locations were computed. The positional accuracy is limited only by the resolution of the data set, which is less than a meter.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Generated the geospatial part of this data set mathematically using the ARC/INFO GRID extension. Added attributes.In order to meet Tutfs University metadata standards:Changed name of file from "latlong" to "WorldLatlong10"Changed citation title from "World Latitude and Longitude Grid" to "Latitude and Longitude Grid World 2010"Added theme keyword "line" to added theme keyword thesaurus "FGDC"Added ISO 19115 Topic Category keywordsAdded LCSH theme keywordsAdded LCNS place keywordsChanged accees constraints from "Access granted to Licensee only." to "Restricted Access Online: Access granted to Licensee only." and added Tufts liability inforamtion.Added Tufts as distributor.Added Publication DateAdded online link

The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted data set from ESRI Data & Maps Volume 1. Removed unneeded attributes. Created ArcGIS layer file (.lyr). Created ArcView GIS legend file (.avl). Ran ArcView GIS Avenue request ExportClean, and created spatial indices.

The following steps were performed by ESRI: Removed all the default ArcInfo attributes -- FNODE_, TNODE_, LPOLY_, RPOLY_, LENGTH, LATLONG_, LATLONG_ID. Created ArcGIS layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices. Converted the data set to SDC.
The following steps were performed by ESRI: Added KILOMETERS attribute and calculated its values. Added MILES attribute and calculated its values.

The following changes were made:File name changed from latlong to WorldLatlong10.Larger Work Citation was added.Keywords and placenames were altered to reflect FGDC standards.Use Constraints, Access, Distribution Liability, Resource, Ordering instructions, Fees, and Contact information were changed to reflect Tufts University requirements.
